The paper deals with the combinatorial complexity of Voronoi diagrams, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves probabilistic analysis (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.DM). The paper specifically focuses on Voronoi diagrams on polyhedral terrains, which falls under the category of computational geometry and geometric reasoning (cs.GR). Finally, the paper presents a result on the expected fatness of a cell in a random planar Voronoi diagram, which is related to computational statistics (cs.SI).
